<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>&nbsp;<u><i><font color="#FFFF00">BASIC CONTROLS:</font></i></u><br>
                  &nbsp; Moves characters onscreen / Moves free cursor on the battle screen / Moves cursor on menu items and boxes that require a response  
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;D-Pad</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Confirms menu commands / Initiates conversation with townspeople / Attacks enemies on the battlefield - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;X Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Opens the character's ability ring - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Circle Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Opens the item menu / On the map screen it opens the save menu - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Square Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Returns to the previous screen during menus / Ends a character's turn during combat - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Triangle Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Activate the free cursor during combat - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;L1 + R1 Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Increase cursor speed - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;L1, R1, R2 or L2 Button (when free cursor is active)</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Change the way a character is facing without moving them during combat - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;L1 or R2 Button + D-Pad</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Opens the options menu screen during combat - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Select Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Opens the character status screen during combat; from the character status screen, pressing the start button will open the accessories menu - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Start Button</font><br><br>
        &nbsp;</td>
	 </tr>
	</table>
